commentary: Holder to Ahmed Shehzad, OUT Has this been taken? Roach does that trick at the fine-leg boundary - he takes the catch, realises his falling over, pops it back in, goes out and comes back to complete the catch. But there is a problem, his left foot was too close the rope and the umpires are looking at it. But they are happy with it, Shehzad has to go. He top-edged his pull shot high and for a moment it looked like it was going to sail over the fielder. Good catch by Roach
shortText: Holder to Ahmed Shehzad, OUT
text: Has this been taken? Roach does that trick at the fine-leg boundary - he takes the catch, realises his falling over, pops it back in, goes out and comes back to complete the catch. But there is a problem, his left foot was too close the rope and the umpires are looking at it. But they are happy with it, Shehzad has to go. He top-edged his pull shot high and for a moment it looked like it was going to sail over the fielder. Good catch by Roach

commentary: Wahab Riaz to DM Bravo, OUT this is the end of Lil Bravo!Another short delivery strikes gold today. Lil Bravo tried to nudge it to the leg side, but it was well directed and it kept rising on to him, the batsman was hit on the shoulder of the bat and it just lobbed up on the leg side. The fielder from square leg runs in and takes a good catch diving forward. It's the Prof there, he makes himself useful. Lil Bravo falls in his teens

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Holder, 2 runs and it's a tie would you believe it! Wahab aims to pitch it fuller on the stumps and doesn't quite succeed, Holder swings and he gets a thick edge that goes past the keeper and races to third man, the throw from Junaid was to the keeper Akmal who didn't collect it at all, not sure what went wrong with Akmal because it wasn't exactly the worst throw
